e regularly exposed to nature are more likely to be happier and healthier; the researchers suggested that spending time in nature can help reduce stress, improve concentration, and boost creativity.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Choice D is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."}]'::jsonb,
